&                     -------------------------------------
                      | QUEUEING DATASETS TO BE BACKED UP |
                      -------------------------------------
$
  A DATASET IS QUEUED FOR LATER BACK UP PROCESSING THROUGH THE ASM2 TSO
  COMMAND.  AN SPF INTERFACE HAS BEEN PROVIDED TO SIMPLIFY USE OF THIS COMMAND.

  A DATASET IS QUEUED FOR BACK UP BY SELECTING OPTION&B$ON THE &ASM2 BACK UP
  UTILITY$MENU.  ENTER THE NAME OF THE DATASET TO BE BACKED UP IN THE&NAME$AREA.
  NORMAL TSO NAMING CONVENTIONS APPLY.  USE SINGLE QUOTES&(')$FOR FULLY
  QUALIFIED NAMES.

  YOU MAY SPECIFY THE NUMBER OF DAYS THE BACKED UP DATASET SHOULD BE KEPT IN
  THE&RETENTION$FIELD.  NOTE:  DEFAULT (AND MAXIMUM) IS&90$.  NOTE THAT THIS
  MAXIMUM DOES NOT AFFECT INCREMENTALLY BACKED UP DATASET RETENTIONS.

